{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UWfncM3vh884FFL4uozdLj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the root cause! The StatefulSet spec has an intentional bug:\n\n```bash\nif [ \"$POD_NAME\" = \"crdb-cluster-1\" ]; then\n  HTTP_ADDR=\"127.0.0.1:8080\";\nelse\n  HTTP_ADDR=\"0.0.0.0:8080\";\nfi; exec /cockroach/cockroach start ... --http-addr=${HTTP_ADDR} ...\n```\n\nFor `crdb-cluster-1`, the HTTP server binds to `127.0.0.1:8080` (localhost only) instead of `0.0.0.0:8080` (all interfaces). The liveness probe uses `httpGet` which accesses the pod IP (not localhost), so it gets \"connection refused\" because the HTTP server isn't listening on that IP!\nPod 1 binds only to localhost while the liveness probe tries to reach it via the pod's IP address, causing repeated probe failures that trigger pod restarts every 45 seconds. The fix is simply to make Pod 1 bind to all interfaces like the others.\n\nI can see the StatefulSet has been partially updated—pods 1 and 2 are running the new revision with the buggy command, while pod 0 is still on the old revision. I need to patch the StatefulSet to remove the conditional logic that restricts Pod 1's HTTP address, so all pods consistently listen on `0.0.0.0:8080`.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6089,"cache_read_input_tokens":50526,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6089},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d6ce834-1657-4ba5-a1f5-1a66b0295e32","uuid":"b56152a1-6fd6-4172-9059-1a55edc41374","request_id":"req_011Ccamt7K9Dz1JRdCS8v2mA"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UWfncM3vh884FFL4uozdLj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found the root cause. The StatefulSet has an intentional bug in the startup command:\n\n```bash\nif [ \"$POD_NAME\" = \"crdb-cluster-1\" ]; then\n  HTTP_ADDR=\"127.0.0.1:8080\";   # ← binds only to localhost!\nelse\n  HTTP_ADDR=\"0.0.0.0:8080\";\nfi\n```\n\nPod 1 (`crdb-cluster-1`) binds its HTTP server to `127.0.0.1:8080` (localhost only), but the liveness probe connects to the pod's IP — connection refused → liveness probe kills the pod repeatedly.\n\nThe fix is to patch the StatefulSet so all pods use `0.0.0.0:8080`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6089,"cache_read_input_tokens":50526,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6089},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d6ce834-1657-4ba5-a1f5-1a66b0295e32","uuid":"0d456476-1e93-4893-b258-c2c6984a8399","request_id":"req_011Ccamt7K9Dz1JRdCS8v2mA"}
