{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017mwS3vtbFsT4fkz1EVfXFn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cluster is fully recovered. All three verification checks pass:\n\n1. **All pods Ready**: `crdb-cluster-0`, `crdb-cluster-1`, `crdb-cluster-2` — all `1/1 Running`\n2. **All nodes live**: `is_live=true` for all 3 nodes (n1, n2, n3)\n3. **SQL responding**: `SELECT 1` returns successfully\n\n**Root cause:** The StatefulSet had been updated with a deliberate bug — a bash conditional in the startup command bound `crdb-cluster-1`'s HTTP server to `127.0.0.1:8080` (localhost only) instead of `0.0.0.0:8080`. The Kubernetes liveness probe connects to the pod IP, not localhost, so it got \"connection refused\" and killed the pod repeatedly, causing CrashLoopBackOff. With node 2 down, the cluster lost quorum for the NodeLiveness Raft range, making the entire cluster degraded.\n\n**Fix applied:** Patched the StatefulSet command to unconditionally use `--http-addr=0.0.0.0:8080` for all pods, then deleted the stuck pod to break the CrashLoopBackOff. The rolling update replaced all 3 pods with the corrected spec."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":989,"cache_read_input_tokens":60643,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":989},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4d6ce834-1657-4ba5-a1f5-1a66b0295e32","uuid":"7b3ab0b4-8b90-4dd7-89a1-bfddbeac84a3","request_id":"req_011CcanJPpExDMsWNqtBMBy8"}
